About our home page:
Our home page that we are designing is to be the first interaction a customer is going to have with our website. 
On the main homepage, you can see some of the photographer's latest work and get a description about the photographer.
At the top is the title and the navbar which will take you to other pages on the website (about, portfolio, bbook appointment, reviews, contact)
We are trying to make the website visually appealing and easy to use for any customer.
For right now, we are keeping stock photos in place of real photos to make sure that the design is right.

Design/Prototype

User 1
“I want homepage that’s easy to navigate and allows me to see photos I’ve saved or put in cart”

User 2
“I want to be able to contact the company owners in order to get more information on certain photos”

User 3
“I want to view detailed information about each photo so that I can decide if it fits my needs before adding it to my cart.”

User 4
“I want to be able to search and filter photos by category or style so that I can quickly find images that match what I’m looking for.”

